1
00:01:00,100 --> 00:01:02,900
=Daughter of Fortune=

2
00:01:02,900 --> 00:01:05,460
(Adapted from the novel
"Phoenix Palace Dream" by Lan Jiujiu)

3
00:01:05,540 --> 00:01:08,460
=Episode 17=

4
00:01:14,799 --> 00:01:15,359
Your Majesty.

5
00:01:15,519 --> 00:01:16,200
You're here.

6
00:01:20,040 --> 00:01:21,480
I specially had

7
00:01:21,840 --> 00:01:23,359
Peng fish sent from Chizhou as tribute.

8
00:01:23,840 --> 00:01:25,040
I knew you'd like it.

9
00:01:26,330 --> 00:01:27,280
Thank you, Your Majesty.

10
00:01:46,079 --> 00:01:47,560
Are Your Majesty's eyes uncomfortable?

11
00:01:48,239 --> 00:01:49,560
Why are you leaning in so close?

12
00:01:51,079 --> 00:01:52,840
You usually seem quite clever.

13
00:01:53,319 --> 00:01:54,799
Your eyes are the problem.

14
00:01:56,879 --> 00:01:57,959
What did I do now?

15
00:01:58,030 --> 00:01:59,470
Please enlighten me, Your Majesty.

16
00:01:59,480 --> 00:02:00,239
No.

17
00:02:00,799 --> 00:02:01,680
Figure it out yourself.

18
00:02:02,159 --> 00:02:03,200
Why pretend to be clueless?

19
00:02:05,879 --> 00:02:07,599
Why is Your Majesty so angry?

20
00:02:07,840 --> 00:02:09,560
Your cheeks are puffed up from it.

21
00:02:10,520 --> 00:02:11,520
Impudent.

22
00:02:12,360 --> 00:02:13,639
You dare pinch my face?

23
00:02:14,520 --> 00:02:15,439
I know my mistake.

24
00:02:15,759 --> 00:02:16,639
The dragon's head,

25
00:02:16,759 --> 00:02:17,479
the dragon's face,

26
00:02:17,479 --> 00:02:18,240
the dragon's mouth,

27
00:02:18,439 --> 00:02:19,319
are to be revered,

28
00:02:19,560 --> 00:02:20,520
not touched.

29
00:02:21,840 --> 00:02:23,199
Of everything about you,

30
00:02:23,840 --> 00:02:25,360
your mouth is the sharpest.

31
00:02:25,410 --> 00:02:26,960
Thank you for the praise, Your Majesty.

32
00:02:27,400 --> 00:02:28,719
I wasn't praising you.

33
00:02:29,000 --> 00:02:29,879
I was scolding you.

34
00:02:30,400 --> 00:02:31,280
I can't hear it.

35
00:02:31,599 --> 00:02:33,360
As long as people call me sharp tongued,

36
00:02:33,360 --> 00:02:34,080
quick witted,

37
00:02:34,080 --> 00:02:34,680
or fierce,

38
00:02:34,879 --> 00:02:36,159
I take it all as praise.

39
00:02:37,919 --> 00:02:39,599
When you face a true enemy,

40
00:02:40,479 --> 00:02:42,850
that sharp tongue of yours
won't be enough to protect you.

41
00:02:46,020 --> 00:02:50,740
♪A fair lady sighs, what eve is this?♪

42
00:02:52,280 --> 00:02:53,319
The enemy's eyes,

43
00:02:53,840 --> 00:02:54,879
the enemy's throat,

44
00:02:55,400 --> 00:02:56,560
the enemy's heart.

45
00:02:57,599 --> 00:02:59,120
Drive it in deeply like this,

46
00:03:00,479 --> 00:03:02,240
then pull it out hard.

47
00:03:03,680 --> 00:03:04,639
Shen Zhinian,

48
00:03:05,599 --> 00:03:07,199
if anyone dares offend you in the future,

49
00:03:07,680 --> 00:03:09,039
use this hairpin

50
00:03:09,599 --> 00:03:10,439
and kill him.

51
00:03:21,319 --> 00:03:22,479
(Yuehui Pavilion)
What are they doing?

52
00:03:25,080 --> 00:03:27,879
Looks like His Majesty is
teaching Lady Shen martial arts.

53
00:03:29,319 --> 00:03:30,599
Martial arts?

54
00:03:31,599 --> 00:03:34,039
Is she planning to fight
beside him on the battlefield too?

55
00:03:38,039 --> 00:03:40,000
Your Highness, let's return to the palace.

56
00:03:48,639 --> 00:03:49,919
Go tell His Majesty

57
00:03:50,439 --> 00:03:51,960
that I won't be attending

58
00:03:52,520 --> 00:03:53,879
his birthday banquet.

59
00:03:54,560 --> 00:03:55,159
Your Highness,

60
00:03:55,479 --> 00:03:56,439
Young Master said

61
00:03:56,840 --> 00:03:58,479
you should worry less

62
00:03:58,479 --> 00:03:59,479
and rest more.

63
00:03:59,759 --> 00:04:01,080
Don't do anything you shouldn't.

64
00:04:01,120 --> 00:04:03,039
So my brother still
has time to worry about me?

65
00:04:03,800 --> 00:04:05,080
All his attention

66
00:04:05,319 --> 00:04:07,039
is on Shen Zhinian now.

67
00:04:09,400 --> 00:04:11,080
Hurry and deliver
the item to His Majesty.

68
00:04:11,439 --> 00:04:12,680
Otherwise later,

69
00:04:13,159 --> 00:04:14,800
His Majesty won't even have time for me.

70
00:04:15,759 --> 00:04:16,519
Yes.

71
00:04:17,759 --> 00:04:18,639
Ah.

72
00:04:18,639 --> 00:04:19,959
So boring.

73
00:04:20,199 --> 00:04:21,990
I really want to leave
the palace and have some fun.

74
00:04:25,480 --> 00:04:26,759
Your Ladyship.

75
00:04:27,199 --> 00:04:28,839
Why are you looking so upset?

76
00:04:29,010 --> 00:04:30,959
His Majesty is taking Shen Zhinian
out of the palace

77
00:04:30,959 --> 00:04:33,399
and wants you to cover
for them before the Dowager Consort.

78
00:04:37,120 --> 00:04:38,680
That slave driver

79
00:04:39,079 --> 00:04:40,480
only knows how to work me to death.

80
00:04:43,319 --> 00:04:44,120
Here.

81
00:04:44,959 --> 00:04:45,800
What is it?

82
00:04:46,240 --> 00:04:47,600
Open it and see.

83
00:04:51,540 --> 00:04:53,920
(Death-exemption medal)

84
00:04:53,920 --> 00:04:55,240
A death-exemption medal?

85
00:04:59,879 --> 00:05:02,199
Didn't you refuse to give me one before?

86
00:05:02,199 --> 00:05:03,920
Why are you suddenly
giving it to me now?

87
00:05:04,090 --> 00:05:05,360
When did I ever say I wouldn't?

88
00:05:06,480 --> 00:05:08,120
The time simply wasn't right yet.

89
00:05:08,300 --> 00:05:09,319
Thank you, Your Majesty.

90
00:05:10,900 --> 00:05:12,680
Your Majesty,
we're about to leave the city.

91
00:05:13,000 --> 00:05:13,399
Mm.

92
00:05:13,500 --> 00:05:14,240
Where are we going?

93
00:05:14,839 --> 00:05:16,480
I'm taking this year's poetry champion

94
00:05:16,920 --> 00:05:18,800
to pay respects
to the owner of Xunlu Pavilion.

95
00:05:20,639 --> 00:05:21,839
Your Majesty's mother?

96
00:05:22,319 --> 00:05:23,000
Mm.

97
00:05:23,580 --> 00:05:26,460
(Imperial Temple)

98
00:05:38,800 --> 00:05:41,839
This is where
Your Majesty lived as a child?

99
00:05:42,360 --> 00:05:43,000
Mm.

100
00:05:44,439 --> 00:05:45,759
After Mother passed away,

101
00:05:46,759 --> 00:05:48,399
I was thrown into a dog kennel.

102
00:06:03,560 --> 00:06:04,519
Your Majesty.

103
00:06:12,199 --> 00:06:13,199
What?

104
00:06:13,759 --> 00:06:15,160
Feeling sorry for me?

105
00:06:15,600 --> 00:06:16,480
Mm.

106
00:06:19,720 --> 00:06:20,959
You're coaxing me again.

107
00:06:21,720 --> 00:06:23,199
I mean it sincerely.

108
00:06:24,720 --> 00:06:26,079
When I was little,

109
00:06:26,360 --> 00:06:28,040
I once raised a mountain sparrow.

110
00:06:28,680 --> 00:06:29,839
Its song was beautiful,

111
00:06:30,079 --> 00:06:31,240
like music from the heavens.

112
00:06:31,720 --> 00:06:34,120
Back then, I only had a bowl
of thin porridge each day,

113
00:06:34,879 --> 00:06:36,120
yet every day,

114
00:06:36,120 --> 00:06:37,639
I still fed it the first spoonful.

115
00:06:39,190 --> 00:06:40,199
What happened after that?

116
00:06:42,010 --> 00:06:43,990
Later, the mountains
were sealed off by heavy snow.

117
00:06:44,160 --> 00:06:45,720
After the last grain of rice was gone,

118
00:06:46,879 --> 00:06:49,160
I fed it with blood from my fingertips.

119
00:06:50,199 --> 00:06:51,079
In the end,

120
00:06:51,360 --> 00:06:52,360
it starved to death?

121
00:06:54,160 --> 00:06:55,319
I ate it.

122
00:06:57,279 --> 00:06:58,040
You ate it?

123
00:07:02,680 --> 00:07:05,079
Are you afraid of me?

124
00:07:09,120 --> 00:07:10,639
I'm not that mountain sparrow.

125
00:07:11,240 --> 00:07:13,519
If one day Your Majesty runs out of food,

126
00:07:13,879 --> 00:07:16,040
I will surely find food

127
00:07:16,390 --> 00:07:18,160
to keep both Your Majesty
and myself alive.

128
00:07:18,639 --> 00:07:19,480
You?

129
00:07:20,319 --> 00:07:21,199
Support me?

130
00:07:21,399 --> 00:07:21,959
Mm.

131
00:07:23,199 --> 00:07:24,319
Though women may seem weak,

132
00:07:24,839 --> 00:07:26,300
for the sake of those they cherish,

133
00:07:26,639 --> 00:07:27,839
they can become

134
00:07:27,839 --> 00:07:29,160
the strongest shield.

135
00:07:32,879 --> 00:07:33,759
I'm like that,

136
00:07:34,160 --> 00:07:35,720
and Your Majesty's mother was the same.

137
00:07:38,199 --> 00:07:38,839
Your Majesty,

138
00:07:40,319 --> 00:07:42,720
may I visit Dowager Consort Qin now?

139
00:07:42,720 --> 00:07:47,060
♪All the spring colors
lean toward one person♪

140
00:07:48,140 --> 00:07:51,759
♪Faint rouge hides
the tenderness in the eyes♪

141
00:07:51,759 --> 00:07:53,279
(Your Highness,)

142
00:07:53,920 --> 00:07:56,199
(I, Shen Zhinian,
pay my respects to you.)

143
00:07:57,240 --> 00:07:59,360
(His Majesty has suffered
greatly along the way.)

144
00:08:00,040 --> 00:08:01,600
(Spirit Tablet of Mother Consort Qin)
(They say a mother and child are always connected at heart.)

145
00:08:02,160 --> 00:08:04,560
(Please visit him
in his dreams more often.)

146
00:08:12,439 --> 00:08:13,839
What did you say

147
00:08:14,000 --> 00:08:14,879
to my mother just now?

148
00:08:15,319 --> 00:08:16,279
I'm not telling you.

149
00:08:16,360 --> 00:08:17,319
It's a secret.

150
00:08:26,879 --> 00:08:28,720
I heard that after ascending the throne,

151
00:08:28,730 --> 00:08:30,560
Your Majesty improved the eternal lamps
in the Imperial Temple.

152
00:08:30,600 --> 00:08:32,000
No matter how fierce the wind,

153
00:08:32,190 --> 00:08:33,399
the eternal lamps never go out.

154
00:08:34,039 --> 00:08:34,840
Seems it's true.

155
00:08:35,679 --> 00:08:38,279
May I ask why Your Majesty is so obsessed
with eternal flames?

156
00:08:43,399 --> 00:08:45,399
There used to
be a punishment in the palace.

157
00:08:46,480 --> 00:08:48,080
Every time an eternal lamp went out,

158
00:08:49,720 --> 00:08:51,159
the prisoner would suffer even more.

159
00:08:51,159 --> 00:08:52,639
Let go of my mother!

160
00:08:53,370 --> 00:08:55,360
- Let go of my mother!
- The eternal lamp has gone out.

161
00:08:55,360 --> 00:08:56,470
- Add twenty lashes.
- Let go of my mother!

162
00:08:56,480 --> 00:08:57,799
Let go of my mother!

163
00:08:59,039 --> 00:09:00,320
Let go of my mother!

164
00:09:00,679 --> 00:09:01,720
Let go of my mother!

165
00:09:05,260 --> 00:09:06,159
Add twenty more lashes.

166
00:09:06,159 --> 00:09:07,559
Stop blowing out the candles!

167
00:09:07,559 --> 00:09:09,680
- Add thirty lashes.
- The eternal lamp can't go out!

168
00:09:12,639 --> 00:09:14,440
No!

169
00:09:14,919 --> 00:09:16,720
Since you like eternal lamps so much,

170
00:09:16,919 --> 00:09:18,720
then I'll give it to you.

171
00:09:25,840 --> 00:09:27,600
No!

172
00:09:34,840 --> 00:09:36,679
If Your Majesty's mother
can see from heaven

173
00:09:36,840 --> 00:09:38,679
that Your Majesty is living well now,

174
00:09:39,399 --> 00:09:41,000
she would surely be happy.

175
00:09:42,240 --> 00:09:43,120
Perhaps.

176
00:09:43,440 --> 00:09:44,399
She definitely would.

177
00:09:45,440 --> 00:09:46,440
Report.

178
00:09:47,279 --> 00:09:48,480
Everything has been prepared.

179
00:09:49,440 --> 00:09:49,960
Let's go.

180
00:09:53,879 --> 00:09:55,639
Why is there a fish tank here?

181
00:09:56,600 --> 00:09:57,720
There are fish.

182
00:10:00,679 --> 00:10:01,879
Peng fish?

183
00:10:02,279 --> 00:10:03,919
Why are there Peng fish here?

184
00:10:05,000 --> 00:10:06,120
When I was little,

185
00:10:06,440 --> 00:10:07,879
I always ran a high fever in winter.

186
00:10:08,720 --> 00:10:09,840
My mother and Madam Lian

187
00:10:09,960 --> 00:10:11,480
personally made this fish tank.

188
00:10:12,120 --> 00:10:15,080
Every so often, Madam Lian
would bring back a Peng fish.

189
00:10:15,720 --> 00:10:16,690
Whenever I had a fever,

190
00:10:16,759 --> 00:10:18,679
she would use
the Peng fish gills to reduce it.

191
00:10:20,080 --> 00:10:22,480
But Peng fish only exist in Chizhou.

192
00:10:22,639 --> 00:10:25,650
And using Peng fish gills to reduce fever
is also a folk remedy from Chizhou.

193
00:10:25,919 --> 00:10:27,399
How did Madam Lian know about it?

194
00:10:28,519 --> 00:10:29,440
I don't know either.

195
00:10:30,240 --> 00:10:31,840
Nor do I know where the fish came from.

196
00:10:33,120 --> 00:10:35,919
I only remember that they were always
covered in injuries.

197
00:10:37,399 --> 00:10:38,440
They sacrificed too much

198
00:10:38,480 --> 00:10:39,440
for my sake.

199
00:10:40,919 --> 00:10:42,399
I hope in their next lives,

200
00:10:43,240 --> 00:10:45,120
they can live free of all worries.

201
00:10:47,960 --> 00:10:49,519
This visit to the Imperial Temple today

202
00:10:50,600 --> 00:10:52,159
truly surprised me, Your Majesty.

203
00:10:53,519 --> 00:10:54,279
Why?

204
00:10:56,080 --> 00:10:57,320
Only today did I realize

205
00:10:58,159 --> 00:10:59,240
that Your Majesty

206
00:10:59,240 --> 00:11:01,360
is also an ordinary person
of flesh and blood.

207
00:11:02,559 --> 00:11:03,639
And only now do I understand

208
00:11:04,600 --> 00:11:05,679
why Your Majesty

209
00:11:06,039 --> 00:11:08,559
became the Nangong Xuanyu you are today.

210
00:11:08,559 --> 00:11:12,020
♪A fair lady sighs, what eve is this?♪

211
00:11:14,300 --> 00:11:19,580
♪You ride the wind,
stunning and graceful♪

212
00:11:23,679 --> 00:11:24,519
Shen Zhinian.

213
00:11:24,759 --> 00:11:25,159
Mm.

214
00:11:27,020 --> 00:11:33,180
♪You do not know that nothing
is sweeter than a fleeting love♪

215
00:11:34,780 --> 00:11:40,100
♪Broken dreams,
listening to the light rain♪

216
00:11:40,480 --> 00:11:41,919
In the future, whatever I have,

217
00:11:42,360 --> 00:11:43,360
I'll give to you.

218
00:11:49,519 --> 00:11:50,759
Why aren't you thanking me yet?

219
00:11:51,300 --> 00:11:54,380
♪Flowers bloom and fall in shame♪

220
00:11:55,039 --> 00:11:55,960
Thank you, Your Majesty.

221
00:11:59,399 --> 00:12:00,600
Why are you walking so fast?

222
00:12:01,080 --> 00:12:02,639
It's getting late.

223
00:12:02,640 --> 00:12:03,790
We should return to the palace quickly.

224
00:12:08,140 --> 00:12:09,279
(Tinglan Palace)

225
00:12:09,279 --> 00:12:10,159
Handan,

226
00:12:10,399 --> 00:12:11,440
go find an escort agency

227
00:12:11,679 --> 00:12:14,080
and send this token to Chizhou
for my maternal grandfather.

228
00:12:14,519 --> 00:12:15,279
What?

229
00:12:15,279 --> 00:12:16,399
Don't ask. Just go.

230
00:12:16,600 --> 00:12:17,360
Yes.

231
00:12:24,620 --> 00:12:27,240
Your Majesty, the people sent to escort
Lady Shen's maternal family

232
00:12:27,519 --> 00:12:28,879
were ambushed at Mount Nanhua.

233
00:12:29,200 --> 00:12:30,530
Their whereabouts are now unknown.

234
00:12:32,090 --> 00:12:33,200
Send more people to search.

235
00:12:33,559 --> 00:12:34,559
I want to see them alive,

236
00:12:34,600 --> 00:12:35,559
or their bodies if dead.

237
00:12:35,679 --> 00:12:36,360
Yes.

238
00:12:40,519 --> 00:12:42,159
Why Mount Nanhua again?

239
00:12:44,679 --> 00:12:46,080
What exactly is hidden there?

240
00:12:46,240 --> 00:12:47,480
This is bad.

241
00:12:47,500 --> 00:12:49,480
If something happens
to Lady Shen's maternal family,

242
00:12:49,480 --> 00:12:51,279
it'll be hard to explain things to her.

243
00:12:51,279 --> 00:12:52,360
Send more men immediately.

244
00:12:52,799 --> 00:12:53,519
Yes.

245
00:12:55,720 --> 00:12:58,120
Your Majesty, Lady Shen sent Miss Handan
to an escort agency

246
00:12:58,120 --> 00:12:59,360
to deliver this item.

247
00:13:03,460 --> 00:13:06,420
(Death-exemption medal)

248
00:13:08,799 --> 00:13:10,399
Who told you to intercept this?

249
00:13:10,400 --> 00:13:11,440
Your Majesty previously ordered

250
00:13:11,440 --> 00:13:12,960
that every item leaving Tinglan Palace

251
00:13:12,960 --> 00:13:15,190
must first be intercepted
for Your Majesty's inspection.

252
00:13:15,360 --> 00:13:16,399
This is bad.

253
00:13:17,860 --> 00:13:22,500
(Death-exemption medal)

254
00:13:30,200 --> 00:13:35,320
♪Broken dreams,
listening to the light rain♪

255
00:13:37,040 --> 00:13:42,280
♪Bitter cold, bringing mist to the eyes♪

256
00:13:43,920 --> 00:13:46,280
♪If we don't meet♪

257
00:13:46,480 --> 00:13:49,720
♪Flowers bloom and fall in shame♪

258
00:13:49,920 --> 00:13:56,440
♪If we meet again,
the peaches will be warm♪

259
00:13:56,800 --> 00:14:03,240
♪Spring breeze passes,
dancing through the years♪

260
00:14:03,600 --> 00:14:09,920
♪Brewing longing,
remembering past lives♪

261
00:14:10,440 --> 00:14:17,120
♪Hard to meet, and just as hard to part♪

262
00:14:17,120 --> 00:14:24,000
♪Who planted the beans
that grew into lotuses?♪

263
00:14:24,240 --> 00:14:30,120
♪Spring breeze passes,
composing the fleeting years♪

264
00:14:31,040 --> 00:14:37,640
♪Clouds on Mount Wu,
no sails on the sea♪

265
00:14:37,800 --> 00:14:44,480
♪Wanting to fold my heart
into a paper kite♪

266
00:14:44,760 --> 00:14:51,200
♪But the ties are too tangled to sever♪

